    <item>
      <title>about</title>
      <link>http://vermeerlt.com/about/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 29 Sep 2016 15:18:04 +0100</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://vermeerlt.com/about/</guid>
      <description>

&lt;h2 id=&#34;features&#34;&gt;Features&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Distribution ray tracing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Disk light sources&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Polygon meshes (+ WF .obj loading)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic texture support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BSDF support, Oren-Nayar diffuse and GGX specular&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Transparency and thin-transparency support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;tech&#34;&gt;Tech&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Vermeer Light Tools is a physically plausible renderer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Vermeer is written in &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.golang.org&#34;&gt;Go&lt;/a&gt; so you&amp;rsquo;ll need that before building.  Binaries will be made available when I&amp;rsquo;m ready for release.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;get-vermeer&#34;&gt;Get Vermeer&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;go get github.com/jamiec7919/vermeer/cmd/vermeer&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;documentation&#34;&gt;Documentation&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please refer to: &lt;a href=&#34;http://vermeer.readthedocs.io/&#34;&gt;The Documentation&lt;/a&gt; for details of the vnf format and useage.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
